<body>

	<h1>Spine Skin Names</h1>

	<input type="file" id="fileInput">

	<script>
		const fileInput = document.getElementById('fileInput');

		fileInput.addEventListener('change', () => {
			const file = fileInput.files[0];
			const reader = new FileReader();
			reader.onload = (event) => {
				const spineJson = JSON.parse(event.target.result);

				const skins = Object.values(spineJson.skins).sort((a, b) => {
					return a.name.localeCompare(b.name);
				});

				const list = document.createElement('ul');
				skins.forEach(skin => {
					const listItem = document.createElement('li');
					listItem.textContent = skin.name;
					list.appendChild(listItem);
				});
				document.body.appendChild(list);
			};
			reader.readAsText(file);
		});
	</script>

</body>
</html>
In this modified version, we use Object.values(spineJson.skins) to extract an array of skin objects, which we then sort using the localeCompare() method on the name attribute of each skin. This ensures that the skins are sorted alphabetically based on their name attribute.We then create a list element, and iterate over the sorted skins array to create a list item for each skin. The textContent of each list item is set to the name attribute of the skin object. Finally, we append the list to the document body.
